Weather API Documentation

Description
The Weather API is a Flask-based web service that provides real-time weather information for a given city. It utilizes the OpenWeatherMap API to retrieve weather data such as temperature, humidity, wind speed, and more.

Base URL
http://localhost:5000 (when running locally)

Endpoints
Get Weather Data
Endpoint: /weather/<city>
Method: GET
Parameters:
<city>: The name of the city for which you want to retrieve weather data.
Description: Retrieves the latest weather information for the specified city.
Example: http://localhost:5000/weather/Jaipur
Response
The API responds with a JSON object containing the following weather data:

temperature_celsius: The temperature in Celsius.
temperature_fahrenheit: The temperature in Fahrenheit.
feels_like_celsius: The "feels like" temperature in Celsius.
feels_like_fahrenheit: The "feels like" temperature in Fahrenheit.
humidity: The humidity percentage.
wind_speed: The wind speed in Km/h.
description: A brief description of the weather conditions.
sunrise_time: The local time of sunrise.
sunset_time: The local time of sunset.

Example response
{
  "temperature_celsius": 25.0,
  "temperature_fahrenheit": 77.0,
  "feels_like_celsius": 27.5,
  "feels_like_fahrenheit": 81.5,
  "humidity": 60,
  "wind_speed": 10,
  "description": "Partly cloudy",
  "sunrise_time": "2023-06-17 05:32:12",
  "sunset_time": "2023-06-17 19:20:37"
}


Usage
To use the Weather API, follow these steps:

Make sure you have Python installed on your system.
Clone the GitHub repository: [insert link to your GitHub repository].
Install the required dependencies by running pip install -r requirements.txt.
Start the Flask server by running python main.py.
Send a GET request to the desired endpoint, providing the city name as a parameter.
Receive a JSON response with the weather data for the specified city.
Technologies Used
Python
Flask
OpenWeatherMap API
Credits
This project utilizes the OpenWeatherMap API for weather data retrieval.
